<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-343-503  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 343 503.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Feb 9 1990 n1361* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Now Learmonth buys loss-maker Jackson for 500,000 pounds sterling.andO;(Learmonth and Burchett Management Systems Ltd., Michael JacksonSystems Ltd.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Learmonth and Burchett Management Systems PLC (acquisitions andmergers)Michael Jackson Systems Ltd. (acquisitions and mergers)IDK Data AB (divestment).andO;Topic:     AcquisitionFinancial AnalysisSoftware Publishers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NOW LEARMONTH BUYS LOSS-MAKER JACKSON FOR #500,000andM;&quot;Prelude to a merger one day?&quot; we asked last October when Learmonth andamp;Burchett Management Systems Plc and Michael Jackson Systems Ltd announcedthat they would work towards merging their software development methodologiesand tools (CI No 1,289) - yes indeed.andP;  Learmonth has now announced that ithas paid #500,000 in cash for Jackson to its previous owner, IDK Data AB,which is quoted on the Stockholm stock exchange.andP;  Turns out that Jackson wasin very bad shape, with a consolidated operating loss of #491,000 for theyear to August 31 last on turnover of #2.49m.andP;  The loss does not tell thefull story, either because it was before interest charges and anextraordinary payment.andP;  The losses are blamed on big start-up losses in theUS and increased overheads in the UK.andP;  Learmonth was clearly not prepared tobuy the company until it had put its house in order, and accordingly, itclosed its Connecticut office and concentrated US Jackson Systems Incactivities at its Washington base - and the costs of this were borne by IDK,which has also assumed liability for Jackson's mortgage in the UK and takenthe costs of cutting UK staff - Jackson had 64 staff worldwide at the end ofAugust, only 47 are joining Learmonth - and the UK staff will relocate toLearmonth's London offices.andP;  Jackson's other subsidiary, included in thesale, is Michael Jackson France SA in Toulouse.andP;  Learmonth says that for thefour months to end-December 1989, draft accounts show that Jackson made anoperating profit of #83,000 in the UK on sales of #792,000, but that theoverseas operations were not yet profitable.andP;  Michael Jackson, who gave hisname to the Jackson Method, joins the Learmonth board as a non-executivedirector.andP;  Separately, Learmonth has acquired a 19% stake in its Australiandistributor Consulit Pty Ltd for #140,500, which also buys an option to takeits holding to a majority in the future.andP;  The Melbourne, Victoria firm hadsales of #1.4m in its last fiscal and forecasts #2.4m for this one.andO;</TEXT></DOC>